description: EU diplomats wake up with a sore head after a number of political grenades from Westminster.
title: Fears for Brexit deal as talks near deadline
title_page: Fears for Brexit deal as talks near deadline - BBC News
maintext: Brussels diplomats say they are willing to make concessions, including on key issues like state aid and fishing but that the UK must do the same, including - and this is as much a bottom line for the EU as it is hard to swallow for the UK - signing up to safeguards for the EU's single market.
